From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tokimo <tokimo@localhost>
Date: Thu, 1 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] fftools: add HEIC tile grid auto-assembly support

Backport tile grid auto-assembly from upstream FFmpeg CLI.

When a HEIC file contains a tile grid stream group, the CLI now
automatically builds an xstack filter graph to assemble the tiles
into a single output image.

Changes:
- ffmpeg.h: Add InputStreamGroup struct and stream_groups/nb_stream_groups
  fields to InputFile, enabling the CLI to track stream groups
- ffmpeg_demux.c: Add DemuxStreamGroup, demux_stream_group_alloc(),
  istg_parse_tile_grid() (builds xstack filter from tile grid metadata),
  istg_add() (dispatches by group type), and cleanup in ifile_close().
  Iterate stream groups during demuxer init.
- ffmpeg_mux_init.c: Add tile grid scoring in map_auto_video() so that
  assembled tile grids compete with individual streams for auto-mapping

Adapted to jellyfin-ffmpeg 7.1.3 API (simplified fg_create signature,
no OutputFilterOptions crop/autorotate support).
